Rostelecom Rallies for 3rd Day Ahead of Expected MSCI Inclusion

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-16T08:27:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/rostelecom-rallies-for-3rd-day-ahead-of-expected-msci-inclusion.html
OAO Rostelecom,  Russia ’s dominant
long-distance phone company, gained for a third day on
expectations it will be added to the MSCI Inc.’s Russia Index
today.  The shares advanced 2.7 percent to 165.87 rubles by 12:02
p.m. in Moscow.  MSCI said on July 28 it intends to add Rostelecom’s shares
to its indexes following the consolidation of its subsidiaries
in May.  “Rostelecom is a widely expected addition to the Russian
universe, with a 3.2 percent weighting,”  Ovanes Oganisian , an
equity strategist, said in an e-mailed report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran in Moscow at 
 jcorcoran13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  